reviewText: Wow 1990 WCW...Ok u get Jim Ross (Talks about college football way toooo much) and Paul E. doing the commentating. JR is much better now and Paul E. is too toned down. Still they do a decent job. The main event is Flair VS Sting for the Title. No spoilers here  but it was a greta match that had a great buildup 2 it. One of the other better matches is Luger defending the US title againist Mean Mark AKA pre-Undertaker. Get this tape just for his rare appearance in WCW. The event also saw JYD and man does he look bad here teaming up with Mr. Wonderful and El Gigante AKA Giant Gonzalez in the WWE taking on the horseman. The match is pretty boring but still good considering the horseman are involved.  No other memorable matches here sorry. Wait if u are a Vader, his debut is right here againist Tom Zenk. I own it but would'nt pay more than 25 for it

reviewText: WCW's Halloween Havoc definitly 1 of the weakest evnets of 1990. So Sting as I said is now The NWA World Heavyweight Champion so the next thing would be have is to have Ric Flair to go against Sting  in a rematch I mean those things are just a done deal. No cause Jim Herd wanted to depush Flair. So after The Great American Bash on The July 21st episode of World Championship Wrestling Sting was challenged by Sid Vicious who was a member of The 4 Horsemen. A few weeks later Sting was set to defend The NWA World Championship against an unknown wrestler named The Black Scorpion. On The August 18th episode of World Championship Wrestling a video was sent out by The Black Scorpion where it was in an all dark room & he was dressed in a middle ages executioner he said that he wanted to destroy Sting. He said don't try & track me down cause my face you wouldn't recognise it cause it is different. He said maybe a little clue could help California 86. Then on The August 25th episode of World Championship Wrestling The Black Scorpion put out another video where he said to look under your bed check the closet he put out another clue he said LA on The Beach. He also said at The Clash Of Champions XII if you beat me I will unmask. So at Clash Of Champions XII Sting defeated The Black Scorpion but after the match there was another guy on the ramp dressed as The Black Scorpion on the ramp. Sid Vicious came down he was mad that his challeng hadn't been accepted Sting told him go to The Championship Commitee & I will be more than happy to give you a title shot. Sid Vicious then beat Sting up on the ramp. On The Septmeber 8th episode of World Championship Wrestling The Black Scorpion sent out another video he was making a pine box I think he said " Sid wants your title I want your life I want your mind." On The September 22nd episode of World Championship Wrestling The Black Scorpion showed up in the crowd then he was gone. It was announced that it would be Sid Vicious vs Sting at Halloween Havoc on The September 29th episode of World Championship Wrestling for The NWA World Championship. During an interview Sid Vicious inturrpted Sting they were going to fight then The Black Scorpion came down to the ring Sting turned around & The Black Scorpion left. On The October 6th episode of World Championship Wrestling Gordon Solie interviewed The Black Scorpion he told him to ask Sting about Tulsa. At a House Show Sting was wrestling The Black Scorpion but Sid Vicious attacked him with a chair & piledrove him on it. The Black  Scorpion sent out another video on The October 13th episode of World Championship Wrestling he said I have your mind now I will wait until Halloween Havoc to continue. They ddin't mention The Black Scorpion until Halloween Havoc. Lex Luger didn't show up to wrestle on The July 28th episode of World Championship Wrestling. They were told it was transportation problems but at the end of the show Tommy Rich said that The Horsemen got him. Setting up Ric Flair vs Lex Luger at Clash Of Champions XII. It was a good match that ended in disqualification when Stan Hansen came in & attacked Luger cause he wanted a shot at The NWA US Championship. On The Septmeber 15th episode of World Championship Wrestling Lex Lex Luger accepted in a great promo. On The September 15th episode of World Championship Wrestling Gary Michael Cappeta was interviewing Ric Flair then Thedore Long came in he told him to get out of Doom's locker room. Doom attacked Arn Anderson on World Wide the following week Doom was cutting a promo Flair & Anderson stormed the ring & got in a fight with  Doom. It was then announced that it would be Ric Flair vs & Arn Anderson vs Doom for The NWA World Tag Team Championship. Nothing came out of there matches they had. The Steiner Brothers defeated The Midnight Express at a House Show fpor The NWA United States Tag Team Championship. They were challenged by The Nasty Boys who debuted at Clash Of Champions XII. There was a contract siging where The Nasty Boys cheap shotted The Steiner's & slammed Scott through a table. So that's about it. The buyrate for this show was a 1.33 that it is down from last years 1.77. So now the matches.DateOctober 27, 1990Attendance8,000VenueUIC PavilionCityChicago, ILRicky Morton & Tommy Rich Def The Midnight Express Bobby Eaton & Stan Lane with Jim Cornette ** & half starsRobert Gibson was injured legitly so Tommy Rich took his place The Southern Boys made an apperance dressed as Jim Cornette. Jim Cornette & Stan Lane would be leaving WCW shortly after this event.Missy Hyatt as Witch cut a promoTerry Taylor Def Wild Bill Irwin ** An ok match Terry Taylor recently retrned to The NWA.Tony Schavonie interviewed Sting about his match with Sid Vicious then the guy that hadn't been mentioned for 2 weeks The Black Scorpion showed up & this is where the angel started having flaws he took a woman they went into a curtain they ended up on the other side on the enterance way & you know what it doesn't take long to figure out that magic trick.Brad Armstrong Def JW Storm * served it's purpose.Tony Schavonie interviewed Jim Cornette he said that The Southern Boys will pay for interfering in their match.The Blaster Masters Blade & Steel Def The Southern Boys Tracey Smothers & Steve Armstrong DUDthis shouldn't have been cut from The VHS cause of Jim Cornette's commentary he talked s  h  it about The Armstong family & The Smother Family. Cornette & Heyman who was doing commentary for the event has 1 last good back & forth. The match itself wass  h  i  t.The Freebirds Michael PS Hayes & Jimmy "Jam" Garvin with Little Richard Marley aka Rocky King Def The Renagade Warriors Mark & Chris Youngblood ** & quarter of a star.Tony Schavonie interviewed Ric Flair, Arn Anderson & Sid Vicious great promos done by all 3 guys.NWA United States Tag Team ChampionshipChampions The Steiner Brothers Rick & Scott Def The Nasty Boys Jerry Sags & Brian Knobs ** & 3 of a quarter starsThe Nasty Boys attacked Rick after the match. This is 1 of The Nasty Boys better matches.Tony Schavonie interviewed The Freebirds they made fun of Robert GIbson's injury.The Junkyard Dog Def The Moondog DUD a s  h  i  t  match.Missy Hyatt cut a promo as a PrincessTony Schavonie interviewed Scott Steiner Jerry Sags attacked Scott he was dressed as a Consession Worker. Then Knobs showed up & they laid Scott out.NWA World Tag Team ChampionshipChampions Doom Ron Simmons & Butch Reed with Thedore Long vs Ric Flair & Arn Anderson ***& a quarter of a starboth teams were counted out. It set up the Street Fight at Starrcade where Ric Flair & Arn Anderson should've went over. But I'll get to that.Stan Hansen cut a hilarious promo. He spit chew on a pumpkin. He said that he's taking The US title all the way back to Texas.NWA United States ChampionshipStan Hansen Def Champion Lex Luger ** & 3 of a quarter starsStan Hansen ended Lex Luger's 17 month reign as NWA US Champion. Dan Spivey made an apperance cause he was Hansen's protoge at the time.Thedore Long was interviewed by Tony Schavonie he said he said that he has proved to The NWA Chicago & Ted Turner is the meanest toughest tag team in WCW & Pro Wrestling.NWA World Heavyweight ChampionshipChampion Sting Def Sid Vicious * & a quarter of a starthis was not good there were a few good spots by Sting & Vicious but the worst of it Ric Flair & Arn Anderson came down to ring side. Sting & Sid Vicious fought to the back then they get back into the ring. Sid gets the win only it wasn't Sting he pinned it was Barry Windham disguised as Sting he had to cut his hair he had the look down. Sting came back hit The Stinger Splash for the win. That was some super s  h  it  t  y booking by Ole Anderson.You have some fun tag team matches on the card. Some funny moments with Jim Cornette. Good commentary with Jim Ross & Paul Heyman. The US Tag title match was decent. The World Tag Team title match was the best match. Ok undercard matches. The US title match was more than decent the right guy went over. The World Championship match was a mess. There was too much going on with Sting he had a fued with The Black Scorpion going on & side fued with Sid Vicious. Why not Sting vs Barry Windham for The NWA World Heavyweight Championship instead. But Halloween Havoc 1990 was a good event. with some Herd era flaws. Starrcade 90 The Collision Course will be the next rasslin PPV.
summary: Halloween Havoc 1990 review 7/10 published & revised on 12/21/11

reviewText: The Tommy Rich/Ricky Morton-Midnight Express match while minus all the unnecessary shenanigans in the finish & you got yourself some classic Midnight Express wrestling with face pace action. The Terry Taylor-Bill Irwin match was not great but pretty good. The Brad Armstrong-JW Storm had some nice power moves but nothing special. The Master Blasters-Southern Boys match was nothing but high-flying moves from the Southern Boys and that's it. The Renegade Warriors-The FreeBirds match was pretty good for a tag team bout. The Steiner Brothers-Nasty Boys-US Tag Team Title match was a hard-hitting,smash-mouth,hardcore,show-stealing brawl. The Junkyard Dog-Moondog Rex match was awful and short thus making it a "Big Lipped Alligator Moment" The Doom-Four Horsemen-World Tag Team title match had good chain wrestling but the ending was awful. The Lex Luger-Stan Hansen-US Title match was good but their Starrcade bout was better. The Sid Vicious-Sting-World title match was slow but stiil a good match even with the dumb "Big Lipped Alligator Moment" ending. Overall,it's a good event with 3 good matches(The Opener,The US Tag Team title match & The World title match) I give this event a 7 out of 10.

If this wasn't bad enough sting comes back and discloses the fraud and then pins sid with a cross body of all things, we're talking about sid right?  Either/Or it was ridiculous, but whats real ridiuclous is the red mat that literally blinds you for 3 hours. still it wasn't all too bad.

reviewText: Event: NWA Halloween Havoc 1990: "Terror Rules the Ring"Date: October 27, 1990Location: Chicago, IllinoisArena: UIC PavilionAttendence: 8,000Non-Televised Match: Tim Horner pinned Barry Horowitz (8:35)....*Non-Televised Match: Rip Rogers pinned Rino Riggins (3:57)....*Tommy Rich and Ricky Morton defeated The Midnight Express (Bobby Eaton and Stan Lane) (20:49) when Rich pinned Lane....****Terry Taylor pinned Bill Irwin (11:47)....**Brad Armstrong pinned JW Storm (5:04)....**The Master Blasters (Blade and Steel) defeated The Wild Eyed Southern Boys (Tracey Smothers and Steve Armstrong) (7:17) when Blade pinned Armstrong....*The Freebirds (Jimmy Garvin and Michael Hayes) defeated Chris and Mark Youngblood (17:28) when Garvin pinned Chris....***United States Tag Team Title Match: Rick and Scott Steiner defeated The Nasty Boys (Brian Knobbs and Jerry Sags) (15:24) when Scott pinned Knobbs to retain the tag team titles....****Junkyard Dog pinned Moondog Rex (3:15)....*World Tag Team Title Match: Doom (Ron Simmons and Butch Reed) Vs. Ric Flair and Arn Anderson fought to a Double Count Out (18:20). Doom retains the tag team titles....*****United States Heavyweight Title Match: Stan Hansen pinned Lex Luger (9:30) to win the title....***World Heavyweight Title Match: Sting pinned Sid Vicious (12:38) to retain the title. ****
